                    <span>As a Sanskrit professor for over 30 years (Emory University, Atlanta, GA and Hindu University of America, Orlando, FL), I find this book both an insult to India and scholarlship in general. This Semite charlatan (babbler, praterer) poses as an "expert" in Hinduism, yet knows no Sanskrit and confuses Jewish words with those of Indo-European origin. In Europe such a charlatan would be laughed out of the university. Purchase her stuff if you wish to waste your $$$ on a charlatan. That is the opinion of one who has been in South Asian studies for over 40 years. </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A good intro book written by someone smarter than you</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
